{{Infobox recurring event | name =Pop Art Festival | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = File:Pop.art.festival.sarajevo.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = active | genre = [[Art festival]] | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "dates=" also works, but do not use both --> | begins = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | ends = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | frequency = <!-- Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Semi-annually, Annually, Bi-annually, 2nd Tuesday of November, etc. --> | venue = | location = Sarajevo | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | country = Bosnia and Herzegovina | years_active = 2017 - present | first = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "founded=" and "established=" also work --> | founder_name = <!-- or | founders = --> | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = <!-- | or sponsors = --> | website = | footnotes = }} The '''Pop Art Festival''' is an annual art festival held in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bihafon.com/2017/04/20/pop-art-festival-uticaj-new-primitivesa-na-popularnu-kulturu/|title=Pop Art Festival: Uticaj New Primitivesa na popularnu kulturu|publisher=bihafon.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/a150325/Video/Info/Almir-Kurt-Kugla-i-Mirna-Dizdarevic-o-Pop-Art-Festivalu.html|title=Almir Kurt Kugla i Mirna Dizdarević o Pop Art Festivalu|publisher=n1info.com}}</ref> It was established in 2017 by the Sarajevo-based cultural association ''Pogon'' in cooperation with the [[Academy of Performing Arts in Sarajevo]], the [[Historical Museum of Bosnia and Herzegovina]] and the iMTM Institute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://faktor.ba/vijest/pop-art-festival-otkriven-mural-ikonama-sarajevske-kulturne-scene-245624|title=Pop Art Festival: otkrivren mural ikonama sarajevske kulturne scene|publisher=faktor.ba}}</ref> It is held in May and lasts for three days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glas.ba/2017/04/21/o-prvom-pop-art-festivalu-u-sarajevu-zenit-losa-elvis/|title=O prvom Pop Art Festivalu u Sarajevu – Zenit, Loša, Elvis…|publisher=glas.ba}}</ref>
The festival was founded with the goal of promoting pop cultural and pop artistic expressional forms, as well as promoting Sarajevan urban culture.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://depo.ba/clanak/159935/pop-art-festival-predstavlja-omaz-sarajevskom-duhu-i-muzickoj-sceni|title=Pop Art Festival predstavlja: Omaž sarajevskom duhu i muzičkoj sceni|publisher=depo.ba}}</ref> It runs programmes for design and comic book art, acting and puppetry, painting and statuary and [[electronic music]] production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/kultura/pop-art-festival-predstavit-ce-omaz-sarajevskom-duhu-i-muzickoj-sceni/170419113|title=Pop Art Festival predstavit će omaž sarajevskom duhu i muzičkoj sceni|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref> Each programme entails workshops and exhibitions, while the music production programme also hosts a DJ competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/kultura/pop-art-festival-predstavit-ce-omaz-sarajevskom-duhu-i-muzickoj-sceni/170419113|title=Pop Art Festival predstavit će omaž sarajevskom duhu i muzičkoj sceni|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref>
The festival also showcases student theatre productions from the Academy of Performing Arts, a radio production seminar and organizes an annual exhibition and panel discussion on [[Hip-hop culture]] that is held in the Obala Open Scene.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslobodjenje.ba/o2/kultura/izlozbe/pop-art-festival-kao-omaz-sarajevskom-duhu-i-muzickoj-sceni-362879|title=Pop Art Festival kao omaž sarajevskom duhu i muzičkoj sceni|publisher=oslobodjenje.ba}}</ref>
