{{Current wildfire}} {{Infobox wildfire |title=South Sugarloaf Fire |image= |caption= |cost= |injuries=1<ref>{{cite news |title=Massive South Sugarloaf Fire Near Owyhee Jumps in Containment |url=http://www.ktvn.com/story/38920587/south-sugarloaf-fire-near-owyhee-still-20-contained |accessdate=1 September 2018 |work=KTVN Channel 2 |date=August 20, 2018}}</ref> |fatalities=0 |reference= |date={{Start date|2018|8|17}} – {{End date}} |location=[[Humboldt-Toiyabe National Forest|Humboldt National Forest]], [[Nevada]] |coordinates={{Coord|41|29|19.971|N|117|32|2.9394|W|display=inline,title}} |pushpin_map=Nevada |pushpin_map_caption=The fires location in southern Nevada |area={{Convert|233516|acre|km2|0}} |buildings= |cause=Lightning }}
The '''South Sugarloaf Fire''' is a currently burning wildfire in the [[Humboldt-Toiyabe National Forest|Humboldt National Forest]] in [[Nevada]], [[United States]]. As of September 1, 2018, the fire had burned a total of {{convert|233,516|acres|km2}} and was 96% contained. The South Sugarloaf fire was first reported on August 17, 2018 and was started by lightning.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/6166/|title=South Sugarloaf Fire Information - InciWeb the Incident Information System|last=helpdesk@dms.nwcg.gov|first=InciWeb developed and maintained by USDA Forest Service, Fire and Aviation Management,|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-09-01}}</ref>
== Timeline ==
=== August === The South Sugarloaf fire was first reported on August 17, 2018 and was started by lightning.<ref name=":0" />
=== September === The fire continued to burn into September. As of September 1, 2018, the fire had burned a total of {{convert|233,516|acres|km2}} and was 96% contained.<ref name=":0" />
== Closures == The [[Nevada Department of Wildlife]] hunting units 061, 062, 071 and 072 are currently closed. The [[United States Forest Service|U.S. Forest Service]] has currently closed around 754,448 acres in the Mountain City and Jarbidge ranger districts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://elkodaily.com/news/hunters-must-obey-sugarloaf-fire-closure/article_ba037e4d-0b09-5008-bf51-dadd06834c0f.html|title=Hunters must obey Sugarloaf fire closure|last=sfeatherston@elkodaily.com|first=SUZANNE FEATHERSTON|work=Elko Daily Free Press|access-date=2018-09-01|language=en}}</ref>
== Evacuations == No mandatory evacuations are in place. However, a number of voluntary evacuations are in place. Areas currently under voluntary evactuons include Wild Horse Reservoir, Bear Creek Road, Jarbidge, Meadow Creek Road, Wildhorse Reservoir, Maggie Summit Road, Mountain City, Wildhorse Estates, Wildhorse Recreation Area and the Gold Creek Area.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://elkodaily.com/news/local/elko-county-fire-tops-acres-more-evacuations-as-entire-forest/article_b83928ee-295c-50be-b9e6-c64ec4f184c8.html|title=Elko County fire makes another surge, better weather expected today|last=DAILY|first=ELKO|work=Elko Daily Free Press|access-date=2018-09-01|language=en}}</ref>
