{{Infobox play | name = The Fire on the Snow | image = | image_size = | caption = | writer = [[Douglas Stewart (poet)|Douglas Stewart]] | characters = [[Robert Falcon Scott]] | setting = [[Antarctica]] | premiere = June 1941 (radio version) | place = | orig_lang = English | subject = [[Terra Nova expedition]] | genre = }}
'''''The Fire on the Snow''''' is a verse play by [[Douglas Stewart (poet)|Douglas Stewart]] about the [[Terra Nova Expedition]] to [[Antarctica]] by [[Robert Falcon Scott]]. It premiered on [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]] radio on 6 June 1941 to great acclaim.<ref>[http://www.liveperformance.com.au/halloffame/leslierees1.html Leslie Rees biography at Live Performance Hall of Fame]</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article146694348 |title="THE FIRE ON THE SNOW.". |newspaper=[[The Narracoorte Herald]] |location=SA |date=3 June 1941 |accessdate=14 September 2014 |page=4 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
==Original Production== The original production was produced by [[Frank Clewlow]] and was to have starred [[Peter Finch]] as Scott, but he joined the army only four days before broadcast, so [[Frank Harvey (Australian screenwriter)|Frank Harvey]] replaced him. Clewlow decided to employ a female actor, [[Ida Elizabeth Osbourne|Ida Osbourne]], as narrator to contrast with the all-male cast. No copy of this original production exists.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/rn/playingthe20thcentury/stories/2011/3087120.htm 'Playing the 20th century – episode three: The Fire On The Snow'], ''Radio National'', 2 January 2011</ref>
==Subsequent Productions== The play has been performed on radio several times since, including a later production starring Peter Finch for Frank Clelow and one directed by [[Tyrone Guthrie]] for the BBC in 1951.<ref>Richard Lane, ''The Golden Age of Australian Radio Drama'', Melbourne University Press, 1994 p 230</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article141743976 |title=THE FIRE ON THE SNOW. |newspaper=[[Barrier Daily Truth]] |location=Broken Hill, NSW |date=15 August 1941 |accessdate=14 September 2014 |page=4 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
The play was published in 1945.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article43480181 |title=Reviews of New Books. |newspaper=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)|The Advertiser]] |location=Adelaide |date=10 February 1945 |accessdate=14 September 2014 |page=4 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
==Original radio cast== *[[Frank Harvey (Australian screenwriter)|Frank Harvey]] as [[Robert Falcon Scott]] *[[John Tate (actor)|John Tate]] as [[Edward Adrian Wilson]] *[[Lou Vernon]] as [[Lawrence Oates]] *[[Peter Bathurst (actor)|Peter Bathurst]] as [[Henry Robertson Bowers|Henry Bowers]] *[[John Alden (actor)|John Alden]] as [[Edgar Evans]] *[[Ida Elizabeth Osbourne]] as narrator
